$interpreted: Nigel: Where did you get these?
Eve: I stole them from the businessman who planned the renovation. I've been keeping an eye on him for a while now...
Nigel: Are these all real?
Eve: It seems... they are tearing down more than just the factory district.
Nigel: Impossible. If the residential area is part of the teardown, they won't promote it so openly. Plus, they said they will be distributing food to...
Eve: But, just look at all the extra areas they plan to tear down...

Nigel: A piece of paper proves nothing. 
Besides, if the renovation is successful, there will be more job opportunities.
Nigel: The children's lives will certainly improve!
Eve: This is no opportunity! They've done nothing except try to exploit us. Have you forgotten how they treated us in the past
Eve: and what they did to your mother...
Nigel: What did you just say!
Eve: If that's the case, I'll protect this place with my own methods!
Nigel: Hey!

Thug: Bro, I think we've traveled far enough?
These oil cans are kinda heavy...

Thug Leader: A bit further won't hurt.
Boss told us that we need to burn it where it really matters.
Thug: But...
Thug Leader: SShhhhh~~
Eve: Tch...
Thug: Bro! We're busted!
Thug Leader: Kill her!
Eve: Who gave you the orders?
Thug: B, Bro...
Thug Leader: You won't get anything from me. I have my pride as a bad guy!

Thug Leader: The person who hired us is Lucky Spencer.
He wants us to burn down the residential area around here
Thug Leader: in order to construct his underground factory!
Eve: I knew it.
Eve: Get lost!
Eve: Lucky Spencer... you're not leaving here alive!
